Julio Iglesias denies physical and sexual assault allegations made against him by two former employees.

[ElDiario.es and Univision Noticias](https://www.eldiario.es/cultura/former-employees-of-julio-iglesias-s-mansions-accuse-the-singer-of-sexual-assault_1_12902422.html) published a joint interview of two women accusing the Spanish singer of assaulting them while working as live-in employees at his Caribbean homes. 

The alleged assaults occurred between January 2021 and October 2021, according to The [Associated Press.](https://apnews.com/article/julio-iglesias-sexual-assault-accusations-dominican-republic-bahamas-e1680de53fee75c067052d885e5403da)

Iglesias called the allegations "absolutely false" in a statement posted [on Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/p/DTjlq18jJsR/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=NTc4MTIwNjQ2YQ==).

 ![Julio Iglesias](https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2026/01/1200/675/iglesias.jpg?ve=1&tl=1)

Spanish singer Julio Iglesias has been accused of sexual assault by two women. (Getty Images)

"With deep regret, I respond to the accusations made by two people who previously worked at [my home](https://www.foxnews.com/category/entertainment/events/celebrity-homes). I deny having abused, coerced or disrespected any woman. These accusations are absolutely false and cause me great sadness," Iglesias's statement, originally posted in Spanish, began.

[**TYLER PERRY HIT WITH NEW $77M SEXUAL ASSAULT LAWSUIT FROM MALE MODEL**](https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/tyler-perry-hit-new-77m-sexual-assault-lawsuit-from-male-model)

"I had never experienced such malice, but I still have the strength for people to know the full truth and to defend my dignity against such a serious affront."

> "These accusations are absolutely false and cause me great sadness."
> 
> — Julio Iglesias

The "Spanish Girl" singer thanked the "many dear people who have sent me messages of affection and loyalty."

"I have felt great comfort in them," Iglesias wrote.

 ![Julio Iglesias smiling](https://a57.foxnews.com/static.foxnews.com/foxnews.com/content/uploads/2026/01/1200/675/julio.jpg?ve=1&tl=1)

Julio Iglesias has denied any physical or sexual assault allegations. (Getty Images)

